<node id="PM (定期保養)">
  <data key="d0">PM (定期保養)</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">PM (定期保養) refers to preventive maintenance activities performed regularly to ensure system reliability and performance.&lt;SEP&gt;PM (定期保養) refers to preventive maintenance, a scheduled type of maintenance aimed at preventing equipment failures and ensuring optimal performance.&lt;SEP&gt;PM (定期保養) refers to the type of maintenance performed, which is periodic maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;PM (定期保養) refers to a preventive maintenance method involving regular servicing and upkeep.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8c09713dbee86ef202f12b324af7f6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e72b71ff65672444ea31e031951b7067&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16690bcfdcdb6d8c3312a19fe520352e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3473c451b90313c144554b6252887062</data>
