<node id="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d0">World Athletics Federation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The World Athletics Federation, formerly known as the International Association of Athletics Federations (IAAF), is the global governing body for athletics. It oversees a variety of significant international competitions, most notably the World Athletics Championships, which are held biennially and encompass a wide array of track and field events. The federation is also responsible for validating world records across various athletic disciplines, ensuring that performances adhere to the required standards and criteria.

In addition to the World Athletics Championships, the World Athletics Federation manages other major international competitions such as the World Indoor Championships and the World Relays. These events are crucial in promoting athletics on a global scale. The federation plays a pivotal role not only in organizing these competitions but also in setting rules and regulations that govern the sport. It is deeply committed to supporting the development of athletics at all levels, from grassroots initiatives to elite competitions.

The World Athletics Federation's responsibilities extend beyond just overseeing championships and validating records. It is instrumental in promoting the sport worldwide, ensuring that athletics continues to thrive and evolve. By setting standards and providing support, the federation helps maintain the integrity and growth of athletics globally.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.</data>
