  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">E客戶 is a customer who interacts with maintenance services in various capacities. E客戶 requests maintenance services and is also the recipient of these services, indicating that they both initiate the need for maintenance and receive the benefits of the services provided.

The descriptions highlight that E客戶 can be involved in maintenance services at different stages: before, during, and after the service provision. Specifically, E客戶 is a customer who has requested maintenance services and is also the customer for whom these services are being performed or have been completed. This suggests a continuous relationship with maintenance providers, from the initial request to the completion of the work.

E客戶 has specific scheduled maintenance work planned for November 14, 2025. This detail underscores the forward-looking aspect of E客戶's role, indicating that maintenance services are not just reactive but also proactive, with future appointments already in place. Additionally, E客戶 requires assistance with various tasks and has maintenance work scheduled, which may include specific needs such as maintenance for their Splunk deployment.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is the customer for whom maintenance services are being provided.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is a customer who has maintenance work scheduled.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is the customer for whom the maintenance service was performed.</data>
