<edge source="World Athletics Federation" target="Noah Carter">
  <data key="d7">79.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Noah Carter, in relation to the World Athletics Federation, achieved a significant milestone when he set a new 100-meter sprint record during a championship event. The World Athletics Federation played a crucial role in this achievement by officially validating Noah Carter's record. This validation underscores the federation's commitment to maintaining the integrity and accuracy of athletic records, ensuring that exceptional performances like Carter's are duly acknowledged and celebrated within the global athletics community. The repeated acknowledgment from multiple sources emphasizes the significance of this record and the World Athletics Federation's role in recognizing and validating such achievements.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation validates Noah Carter's new 100m sprint record set at the championship.</data>
  <data key="d9">athletic governance,athletics governance,competition oversight,governing body,record validation</data>
